festival.introText:
Mad Cool is one of Europe's biggest and best music festivals, held each summer in the Spanish capital.

With a lineup that brings international superstars from an array of genres to Madrid – rock giants at the top of the bill, indie and pop favourites elsewhere, and a selection of underground electronic music's hottest acts among them.

Having consistently grown in scale – be it the performers, crowds, or production – the festival has quickly found its place among the continent's elite, despite only hosting the first edition in 2016, offering well over 100,000 music fans the chance to soak up the Spanish sun and witness their musical heroes doing what they do best.

faqs.question: When does Mad Cool Festival take place?
faqs.answer: Mad cool festival takes place between the Thursday 6th - Saturday 8th July 2023.

faqs.question: I would like to upgrade my ticket to VIP, what should I do?
faqs.answer: Upgrades are managed directly by the ticketing agents. Please get in touch with the ticketing agent you bought the ticket from or send an email to info@madcool.es and we will sort it out for you.

faqs.question: Do you have to be of legal age to gain access to Mad Cool?
faqs.answer:
If you are over 16 you will be able to enter the site without having to be accompanied. But if you are between 16 and 17, you will be required to register your bracelet online once you receive it at home.

If you are under the age of 16 you will have to be accompanied by an adult. Also, either a parent or legal guardian will be required to complete the online registration of your bracelet.

Entrance is free for children under the age of 8 (always accompanied).

faqs.question: Can you camp at Mad Cool Festival?
faqs.answer: Unfortunately, Mad Cool is not a camping festival, so there is no official or on-site camping. However, accommodation can be booked as an add on.

faqs.question: Are payment plans available?
faqs.answer: Yes, payment plans are available for the festival.
